## <a id="reqs"></a> Requirements

To use <%= vars.product_short %>, you must have:

* Access to the <%= vars.product_short %> Early Adopter Program.
* A Kubernetes cluster configured with RBAC. To configure your Kubernetes cluster with RBAC, see [Using RBAC Authorization](https://kubernetes.io/docs/reference/access-authn-authz/rbac/).
To use groups, configure the cluster with a backing identity provider such as OpenID Connect (OIDC). For more information,
see [Authentication strategies](https://kubernetes.io/docs/reference/access-authn-authz/authentication/#authentication-strategies).
* A sandbox environment for testing.
* A Docker image registry for image relocation.

## <a id="limitations"></a> Limitations

<%= vars.product_short %> has the following general limitations:

* <%= vars.product_short %> is in alpha. The product may change in later versions.
* You can use <%= vars.product_short %> with any Kubernetes distribution. Given the number of
Kubernetes vendors, versions, and configurations, not all distributions are tested with
<%= vars.product_short %>. Succesfully tested versions include Kubernetes v1.12 through v1.17.
* <%= vars.product_short %> upgrades are currently not supported. To test a newer version, delete the previous version
first.

